there
were
an
instantaneous
impression
in
her
favour,
as
if
his
eyes
received
the
truth
from
hers,
and
all
that
had
passed
of
good
in
her
feelings
were
at
once
caught
and
honoured.
He
looked
at
her
with
a
glow
of
regard.
She
was
warmly
gratified
and
in
another
moment
still
more
so,
by
a
little
